{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01F1CC8PsfyFsDu6WE5cGgzf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the structure:\n\n**SH1 sheet** has invoice blocks:\n- Row 1: \"INVOICE NO\" header, Row 2: \"A7179\", then items until TOTAL row at row 5\n- Row 9: \"INVOICE NO\" header, Row 10: \"A7180\", then items until TOTAL row at row 14\n- Row 18: \"INVOICE NO\" header, Row 19: \"A7185\", then items until TOTAL row at row 23\n- Row 27: \"INVOICE NO\" header, Row 28: \"A7188\", then items until TOTAL row at row 33\n\n\n- Row 36: \"INVOICE NO\" header, Row 37: \"A7189\", then items until TOTAL row at row 41\n\nNow I'm looking at the DATA sheet where column E identifies which source sheet each row belongs to. I need to match rows where column E says \"SH1\" and replace their column D values with the corresponding invoice numbers from SH1 in sequence. Rows with other sheet names like \"MNHTY\" should keep their original values. The FAKE sheet shows what the final result should look like. So within the SH1 group, I need to identify the subgroups separated by TOTAL rows—each subgroup gets assigned the next sequential invoice number from SH1, while the MNHTY rows retain their original invoice numbers.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6404,"cache_read_input_tokens":13939,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6404},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4386e001-0be4-4a4d-9acc-2641d341ff18","uuid":"7a8a3833-1c21-4611-9f94-1de1af82f1cd"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01F1CC8PsfyFsDu6WE5cGgzf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Jvx9yHPgDq8ZBrGVpWUS6W","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport openpyxl\n\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook('input.xlsx')\nsh1 = wb['SH1']\ndata = wb['DATA']\n\n# Extract invoice numbers from SH1 in order\ninvoice_numbers = []\nfor row in range(1, sh1.max_row + 1):\n    if sh1.cell(row, 4).value == 'INVOICE NO':\n        inv = sh1.cell(row + 1, 4).value\n        if inv:\n            invoice_numbers.append(inv)\n\nprint(\"Invoice numbers from SH1:\", invoice_numbers)\n\n# Identify groups in DATA by TOTAL rows, assign invoice numbers to groups matching \"SH1\"\n# A group is: consecutive rows sharing same E value, ending with a TOTAL row\nsh1_idx = 0  # index into invoice_numbers\n\n# Walk DATA rows 2..max_row, identify groups\nrow = 2\nwhile row <= data.max_row:\n    sheet_name = data.cell(row, 5).value  # column E\n    if sheet_name == 'SH1' and sh1_idx < len(invoice_numbers):\n        inv = invoice_numbers[sh1_idx]\n        # Fill this group until TOTAL row\n        r = row\n        while r <= data.max_row:\n            if data.cell(r, 5).value == 'SH1':\n                data.cell(r, 4).value = inv\n                if data.cell(r, 1).value == 'TOTAL':\n                    r += 1\n                    break\n                r += 1\n            else:\n                break\n        sh1_idx += 1\n        row = r\n    else:\n        # Not matching SH1 - keep original, skip this group\n        r = row\n        while r <= data.max_row:\n            if data.cell(r, 1).value == 'TOTAL':\n                r += 1\n                break\n            r += 1\n        row = r\n\n# Verify\nfor r in range(2, 18):\n    print(f\"D{r} = {data.cell(r, 4).value}, E{r} = {data.cell(r, 5).value}\")\n\nwb.save('output.xlsx')\nprint(\"\\nSaved output.xlsx\")\nPYEOF\n","description":"Generate output.xlsx with invoice numbers filled in"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6404,"cache_read_input_tokens":13939,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6404},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4386e001-0be4-4a4d-9acc-2641d341ff18","uuid":"218a59ce-78c4-4fa1-bd72-283f8f640fa4"}
